-{"id":"franken_numpy-7o9k","title":"PORT: numpy.exceptions submodule parity","description":"fnp_python is missing the numpy.exceptions submodule. Numpy 2.x consolidates the long-tail warning + error classes (ComplexWarning, VisibleDeprecationWarning, ModuleDeprecationWarning, RankWarning, TooHardError, DTypePromotionError, AxisError) into numpy.exceptions and the top-level numpy namespace forwards to it. Mirror that submodule on fnp_python.exceptions with eager re-export from numpy.exceptions when available + an explicit fallback list (so embedded interpreters without numpy at module init still expose the class names). Also re-export each name on the top-level fnp_python module so 'from fnp_python import AxisError' works the same way 'from numpy import AxisError' does. Add a parity test verifying __all__ matches numpy verbatim and every class is the same object as numpy.exceptions's.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T13:39:35.678201586Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:40:00.616327713Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_numpy-7o9k","title":"PORT: numpy.exceptions submodule parity","description":"fnp_python is missing the numpy.exceptions submodule. Numpy 2.x consolidates the long-tail warning + error classes (ComplexWarning, VisibleDeprecationWarning, ModuleDeprecationWarning, RankWarning, TooHardError, DTypePromotionError, AxisError) into numpy.exceptions and the top-level numpy namespace forwards to it. Mirror that submodule on fnp_python.exceptions with eager re-export from numpy.exceptions when available + an explicit fallback list (so embedded interpreters without numpy at module init still expose the class names). Also re-export each name on the top-level fnp_python module so 'from fnp_python import AxisError' works the same way 'from numpy import AxisError' does. Add a parity test verifying __all__ matches numpy verbatim and every class is the same object as numpy.exceptions's.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T13:39:35.678201586Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:45:36.479397195Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:45:36.477488131Z","close_reason":"numpy.exceptions submodule mirrored on fnp_python.exceptions with eager re-export, PEP-562 lazy fallback, top-level forwards, and 6-name fallback __all__ (RankWarning dropped in numpy 2.x). Test exceptions_submodule_matches_numpy passes; lib suite 474/474. Code landed via dc2fcb6 (cross-merged with u98f) + 17fb294.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
