 {"id":"franken_numpy-7qp9","title":"[MOCK] fnp-conformance fixture unwraps should use expect() with context (42 sites)","description":"mock-code-finder audit (audit_numpy_mocks.md, 2026-04-22) found 42 production-code .unwrap() calls in fnp-conformance fixture/oracle builders. NOT mocks or stubs — unwrap on statically-correct invariants (non-empty Vec, matching DType::F64, constant seeds) — but they lose diagnostic context if the invariant is ever violated during future refactors.

Sites:

crates/fnp-conformance/src/lib.rs (25 sites, all pattern:
  UFuncArray::new(vec![v.len()], v, DType::F64).unwrap()
  lines 13147, 13151, 13155, 13159, 13177, 13181, 13185, 13189,
        13207, 13211, 13215, 13219, 13233, 13237, 13241, 13245,
        13271, 13275, 13279, 13283, 13297, 13301, 13305, 13309, 13319

crates/fnp-conformance/src/bin/dump_expected.rs (17 sites, pattern:
  Generator::from_pcg64_dxsm(seed).unwrap() and distribution helpers:
  dirichlet, noncentral_chisquare, noncentral_f, multinomial, zipf, etc.)

Fix: replace .unwrap() with .expect("fnp-conformance fixture: <reason>") so a future refactor that breaks the invariant surfaces a readable message instead of a bare Option::unwrap panic. Purely diagnostic improvement; no semantic or behavioral change.

Verification: cargo test -p fnp-conformance; cargo run -p fnp-conformance --bin dump_expected.

Low priority — these paths are never hit in production, only in oracle/benchmark capture.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:18:53.995974530Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T11:17:49.661364559Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T11:17:49.659529874Z","close_reason":"Closed by cc-numpy — 42 fnp-conformance fixture unwraps (25 in src/lib.rs, 17 in src/bin/dump_expected.rs) replaced with .expect() carrying context per bead spec. Diagnostic-only; no semantic change; build verified via rch cargo check. Commit 0761a2d.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
